}}'''StarlightLab''' is a map created by Bia Kawaii BR for Space Jam 3, where she shows her passion for space and her knowledge in the space field —one of Bia Kawaii BR's greatest passions!

==Design==
StarlightLab is a map originally created for [[Space_Jam_2026|Space Jam 3]], where players begin their journey with a simulated moon landing, being transported alongside their crew to a fully functional dome base on the lunar surface.

The dome's design balances functionality and comfort. On one side, players can unwind in a cozy living space featuring a cinema room, a fully equipped kitchen, a comfortable lounge for watching films and videos, and private bedrooms with a breathtaking view of the moon. On the other side, players can customize their space exploration vehicle, track missions and progression, unlock achievements, and personalize their helmet — which activates automatically upon leaving the dome to explore the vast 15km² map, complete with ramps, time trial races, and hidden secrets. No spoilers here!

==Map overview==
A world designed for both fun and relaxation, StarlightLab offers activities for every type of player:

* '''Cozy living spaces''': A fully equipped kitchen, a cinema room, and a comfortable lounge provide the perfect environment to relax and socialize with friends after a long exploration session.
* '''Private bedrooms''': Comfortable rooms with a direct view of the lunar surface, offering players a quiet space to rest their avatars and enjoy the atmosphere.
* '''Exploration & progression''': Players can customize their space vehicle and helmet, take on missions, and track their progress — all from within the dome before heading out to explore.
* '''[https://vrchat.com/home/group/grp%20fa1b4dab-3c39-4dfc-b5ed-9453e3d20b9c/store VIP area]''': An exclusive space available for players seeking a more private experience.
* '''Game room''': A dedicated area featuring activities for all types of players.
* '''Cinema/media room''': A space where players can watch videos and films together, perfect for community gatherings.
* '''Time trial races''': Players can compete against their friends in time trial races across the lunar surface, testing their skills and pushing their exploration vehicles to the limit.

==Performance==
One of StarlightLab's greatest strengths — shared across all of Bia Kawaii BR's maps — is its strong focus on performance optimization, ensuring the map runs smoothly on any modest PC without any compromise to visual quality.